args:
During the reign of King Aurelius

The Kingdom of Alberia
Sol Alberiaâ€”New Town
Damnation! I'm too late here too!
(But I still can't give up. I have to save\neveryone I can, even if it's just one more!)
Ah! I think that sound came from the\nsouthern district!
It sounded like a tremendous explosion.\nI must hurry!
No survivors over here. They're in the\nhands of the Goddess nowâ€”the best we\ncan do is bring in the clergy later.
Hey! There's a child alive over here!\nI think his parents protected him!
How could this have happened when the\nknights themselves were here...?
Because we did not have enough of us for\nthe scale of the problem.
Harle! Cecile! What are you doing here?
After I asked HQ for instructions, I came\nto Old Town with as many people as we\ncould muster. But...we failed...
If I were a little stronger, maybe I could\nhave saved more people...

Yes, she is quite correct. With the aid of
another strong knight, we would likely
have been able to push aside the rubble
before it fell.
Had you not chosen the foolish route, Leif,\nwe could have saved some of those lives.
Quiet, Harle! Leif was trying to help!
Harle is right. It's my fault that those\npeople are dead.
I boasted of disarming all the explosives,\nyet failed to do so. As a result, I was able\nto help no one.
In the end, all my talk of ideals was\nmerely wind. I did nothing to actually\nlive up to them.

Shhh. Easy, Leif. Don't try to move, okay?
You're at the inn behind the assembly hall.
Do you remember anything from before
you lost consciousness?
I...I was investigating the incident, and...\nAh! Callan!
He sustained some burns, but will live.\nHe's being treated at the church.
Hey, but are YOU okay? You were tossing\nand moaning something fierce while you\nwere out.
Physically, yes. I am well. But my mind...\nI fear I was reliving the experience back\non that day once more.
Ever since that day, I worried my blustery\nwords of idealism were without meaning\nand strove never to repeat my mistakes.
I also attempted to make what amends I\ncould by supporting the facility that gave\naid to the victims.

And when I took up the position of the
White Sparrow captain and gained many
reliable subordinates, I started to believe
again that my dream might be possible.
But now I find myself right back\nwhere I started!
Perhaps, in the final analysis, I truly am\nincapable of realizing my ideals.
This kind of talk isn't like you, Leif.\nYou normally shine so brightly that...\nthat you kind of scare me.
Listen, Leif. Ideals are distant. Ephemeral.\nI know that lesson so well it hurts.
They're pretty, but they're so easy to break.\nLike a castle made of glass.
I'm sorry. I know you have had much pain\nin your own life.
You're right. I did a lot of terrible things in\nthe name of loyalty, and in doing so lost\nsight of my own sense of honor.

But since reuniting with you, I feel like I've
gotten back on my feet in a way. Like I can
look towards knighthood and ideals again,
and like I WANT to do it.
But doing all of that right away? Never.\nNo matter how much I may want to,\nI have to conquer my fear first.
All of this because I had my ideals\nshattered and suffered a setback...\nWhat a coward I am.
Your ideals were shattered back then,\nbut you never gave up.

You got a front-row seat to seeing the gap
between ideals and reality, but you still
kept believing in them and working hard
enough to practically cough up blood.

That's why your eyes still sparkle.
Even now, where you're allowing yourself
a rare moment of doubt, your flame still
hasn't burned out.
And that means you haven't given up.
You're right. I haven't. And I won't.
No matter how painful and thorny the road\nmay be, I won't give up. That is my true,\nunvarnished intention.
OKAY, STOOOOOP! Look, I know I was\nencouraging you and all, but I can't deal\nwhen you get all bright and shiny noooo!
Hoooo! Yeah, I'm all good now. So long as\nI've got my Manachew, I'm solid as a rock.
Looks like you've cooled off a bit too.
Thanks to you. Your fine words of\nencouragement have enabled me to\nrise to my feet once more.
I can still act. I have dreams to make\ninto reality, and this is not the time nor\nthe place to be losing heart.
Um, it's me. My treatment is done,\nso I wanted to come see you.
They're okay. I mean, everything hurts,\nbut I can still walk, and they said I just\nneed to rest for a while and I'll recover.
Then the dark cloud has a silver lining.\nStill, I must apologize, for it seems all I\ndo is fail in my attempts to protect you.
Don't apologize, Leif! It was my fault for\njust blundering in there!
Yet the truth remains that I could not\nprotect you, just as I could not protect\nyour parents all those years ago.
But I will not make the same mistake\nagain. I will solve this crimeâ€”I swear it.
